{
  "stem": "3453.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they got-- they were-- they left it-- they left, to leave down there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They didn't have to move out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so at night, the people who used-- they did-- we had a curfew, 8 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They didn't have no curfew.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So at night, we used to hear some trucks would come in, into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we didn't know if this is a truck that was coming in to-- to stop at the house to drag out people to be killed or whatever it is.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But all they were-- some-- the truck belonged to a Christian family who was coming at night around 10:00, 11 o'clock from his work and going back home.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in this fear, that's the way we lived.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In-- what do you mean, to the camp-- the camp?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Was-- was-- we were taken out from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, we had to come to the square of the ghetto each, the whole-- all the people from Sarny ghetto had to come.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then there was a guy, a German, and I will never forget his-- his face.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was standing with a little table in front of him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was alphabetically calling out names, putting them into-- into groups of 30-40, putting them behind the gate, and right away be surrounded by Germans and Ukrainians.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they take them away right away someplace.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I, my family name was Szyr.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I was almost at the end to leave the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's exactly.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They took us down there to be executed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
